      {
        "id": 1851007,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-01-30T23:12:22.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Agree this is consistently a special bottling. There is a particular herbal /spice signature to this wine that I have trouble pinning down.</p>\n<p>Nice to have a source for Pinot Gris made in this style outside of Alsace, a region to which climate change has not, to my mind, been kind.</p>\n<p>As for Eyrie longevity, the 1985 Pinot Noir South Block I tasted last year was one of the best North American Pinot Noirs I have ever encountered.</p>",
